name: Unicode.NumericType
desc: The numeric type of a scalar.

items.name: case decimal
items.desc: A digit that is commonly understood to form base-10 numbers.

items.name: case digit
items.desc: A digit that does not meet the requirements of the decimal numeric type.

items.name: case numeric
items.desc: A digit that does not meet the requirements of the decimal numeric type or a non-digit numeric value.

items.name: func hash(into: inout Hasher)
items.desc: Hashes the essential components of this value by feeding them into the given hasher.

items.name: static func != (Unicode.NumericType, Unicode.NumericType) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two values are not equal.

items.name: static func == (Unicode.NumericType, Unicode.NumericType) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two values are equal.
